What you need to know:

Kasskass said that the inaugural football clinic was an eye-opener and he will plan to hold more clinics to enlighten the boys on the dangers of drugs and crime."The young players hail from areas that are not safe for them and face a lot of bad influence and as former football stars, the only way we can give back to the society is giving them tips to become better football players and citizens, by encouraging them to pursue their education vigorously," said Kasskass.